VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'depolarization type mechanics in a biofilm. So, bacteria like to live in a community often with different members and some of them like to talk to the biofilm to tell them what\'s going on. In this case, they believe that they\'re'

[02:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'informing the other bacteria to slow their metabolic rate because we just don\'t have enough food here for everyone. And it involves depolarization. It looks like nerves. This is This is wild. This tells me that the organization of our brain, the'

